Conducted proactive threat hunting activities across collected Apache and system logs to identify hidden or suspicious behaviour not immediately flagged by alerts.

Activities included:

Searching for unusual IP connections and repeated failed authentication attempts
Investigating anomalous traffic patterns across time windows
Identifying potential persistence or reconnaissance activity
Using hypothesis-driven investigation techniques (e.g., “What if an attacker is scanning internally?”)
Correlating multiple log sources to validate suspicious behaviour

This process improved analytical thinking and strengthened the ability to detect stealthy or low-and-slow attacks that bypass traditional alert systems.
